frameDefinitions: A particular Binding_principle is (or is not) operative, that is, any obligations, restrictions, and any other aspects of the Binding_principle are (or are not) in effect.
Through use, a Resource is diminished in quality or quantity (up to complete attrition) such that it becomes less capable of sustaining future use.
An Entity persists in a stable situation called a State
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
An Earner receives Earnings by providing Goods to a Buyer; providing the Goods also generally entails a cost, which may or may not be included in the consideration.
An Entity is in a specified State.
frameExamples: This law will only become in <t>effect</t> during the last three weeks of the year.
My entire life savings is <t>depleted</t> due to university and medical bills.
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
This reflects the 15 % jump in <t><fex name='Earnings'>earnings</fex></t> over 1994 .
Some of the classics were in excellent <t>condition</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is the law, contract, principle, or other (set of) obligations that is (or is not) operational.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is in effect.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is or is not operational.
The <fen>Resource</fen> is a physical entity or an ability to perform work that was used in an earlier process, typically in pursuit of a goal.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
The <fen>Earner</fen> is involved in a transaction or set of transactions as the party that receives payment.
<fen>Earnings</fen> are the money given to the <fen>Earner</fen> in a transaction, generally in exchange for <fen>Goods</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The entity whose <fen>State</fen> is specified and/or evaluated.
A relation in which the <fen>Entity</fen> participates or a property that the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses.
listRoleExamples: Once <fex>the treaty</fex> is in effect, US port authorities and the Coast Guard will monitor compliance by checking any yacht 79 feet or longer.
All patent applicants and owners should be aware of the current uncertainty as to what patent fees will be in effect <fex>on October 1, 1998</fex>
This promotion is void <fex>in the state of Florida</fex>.
She made a lot of money <fex>in Africa</fex> .
It was stressed that no diagnosis of <fex>my</fex> state of health would be made, so all she was doing was describing how she felt my 'aura' to be.
Despite being in a state <fex>of considerable disrepair</fex>, the building is surprisingly roomy inside and has a pleasant feel to it.
